  m_Name: If statements
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  articleName: If statements
  articleText: "There are four types of conditional statements in C#, used for decision-making
    in programs: if, else, else if, and switch. For the sake of brevity, this game
    will cover only the first three.\r\n\r\nThe syntax for an if statement is this:\r\n~if(condition)`\r\n~{`\r\n 
    ~//code to be executed`\r\n~}`\r\n\r\nWhere ~condition` is a bool like ~true`
    or ~false` or a boolean expression like ~5 < 10`."
  articleExample: "~if(true)\r`\n~{\r`\n~  Bot.say(\"True!\"); //G4wain says \"True!\"\r`\n~}\r`\n~if(false)\r`\n~{\r`\n~ 
    Bot.say(\"True!\"); //does not execute, condition is false`\n~}\r`"
